# The Brutal Truth About AI Engineer Interviews in 2026
### What Interviewers Actually Look For

Sravan Rekandar  
Founder – Drishya AI Labs  
20+ Years in Software Engineering

---

# Opening Story (60 Seconds)

A candidate once came for an interview.

Great resume.  
Good academic scores.  
GitHub full of projects.

Everything looked impressive.

So I asked a simple question.

> “Can you explain how this function in your project works?”

Silence.

Slowly the truth appeared.

The project was copied from a tutorial.  
Some parts were generated by ChatGPT.

The code worked.

But the candidate **did not understand it**.

And that is the brutal truth about software interviews in 2026.

> Tools can generate code.  
> Interviews reveal whether **you understand it**.

---

# The Illusion Students Believe

Many students believe:

- Learn a programming language → get a job
- Solve LeetCode problems → get a job
- Complete assignments → learning is done

Reality is different.

> Interviews test **thinking, honesty, and consistency**.

Not just coding.

---

# The First Filter: Trust

Before employers evaluate your skills, they evaluate **trust**.

Companies are asking:

- Can we trust this person with our systems?
- Can this person take responsibility?
- Does this person understand their work?

Signals that build trust:

- academic discipline
- consistent learning
- explainable projects
- honest problem solving

---

# Why Academic Foundations Matter

Many students say:

> “Marks don't matter.”

Marks are not everything.

But they represent:

- discipline
- consistency
- exposure to fundamentals

Academic systems may not be perfect.

But they represent a **long process of learning essentials**.

Respect:

- your college
- your faculty
- the learning process

> College teaches essentials.  
> Excellence is your responsibility.

